description: Ban AI agent mentions in commits, docs, and code
alwaysApply: true
---

# No agent attribution

Never add mentions of yourself, AI, or code-generation tools anywhere in the project:

- commit messages and git trailers (`Co-authored-by`, `Signed-off-by`, etc.)
- PR and issue descriptions
- README, AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md, and any documentation
- code comments
- changelog and release notes

Forbidden: "Generated by AI", "Co-authored-by: Cursor/Claude/Copilot/ChatGPT", references to Cursor, Claude, Copilot, ChatGPT, OpenAI, Anthropic as authors.

Commits and text should read as if written by a human developer.
